        "subtitle": "Predict focus score using sleep, caffeine, environment & task type",
        "description": "I created this dataset to explore how lifestyle and environmental factors influence human productivity, measured as a **\"Focus score\"** on a scale from **0 to 100**. The data was generated using logic-driven simulation techniques to mimic realistic patterns based on sleep, caffeine intake, environmental conditions, and work habits.\n\nThis dataset is ideal for practicing **regression modeling, feature engineering, and end-to-end ML pipelines**. Feature correlations are intentionally embedded to help learners understand how structured inputs can drive model performance.\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udcc8 Use Cases : \n\ud83d\udd39Regression modeling\n\n\ud83d\udd39Feature importance analysis\n\n\ud83d\udd39EDA & preprocessing practice\n\n\ud83d\udd39ML pipeline building\n\n\ud83d\udd39Hyperparameter tuning\n\n---\n\n### \ud83d\udca1 Useful? Drop a quick upvote to support!\n\n\n=== About this file ===\n\nAbout this file\nFormat: CSV (Encoding: UTF-8)\nRows: 10,000\nColumns: 6 (including target focus_score)\nMissing Values:  Present\n\n\n=== Columns & descriptions ===\n\nhours_slept: Total hours slept in the last 24 hours (range: 3\u201310)\ncaffeine_mg: Total caffeine intake in mg (range: 0\u2013500)\nnoise_level_db: Ambient noise level (in decibels)\ntask_type: Type of work: Creative, Analytical, Routine, Managerial\nwork_environment: Where work happens: Home, Office, Cafe, Co-working\nfocus_score: Final focus/productivity score (0\u2013100)\n",
